---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Themes">
  <h2>Themes</h2>
  <p>
    Rep-li-bot includes four carefully crafted themes to customize the look
    and feel of your apps.
  </p>

  <h3>Available Themes</h3>

  <h4>Meadow (Default)</h4>
  <p>A fresh, natural palette perfect for productivity apps.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Accent: <code>#7ac8ab</code></li>
    <li>Background: <code>#f5f3eb</code></li>
    <li>Text: <code>#203039</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Terminal</h4>
  <p>A classic terminal aesthetic with dark background and green accents.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Accent: <code>#4ade80</code></li>
    <li>Background: <code>#0d1117</code></li>
    <li>Text: <code>#e6edf3</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Paper</h4>
  <p>A clean, minimal light theme with indigo accents.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Accent: <code>#6366f1</code></li>
    <li>Background: <code>#fefefe</code></li>
    <li>Text: <code>#1f2937</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h4>Sunset</h4>
  <p>A warm, inviting theme with orange accents.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Accent: <code>#f97316</code></li>
    <li>Background: <code>#fff7ed</code></li>
    <li>Text: <code>#431407</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Changing Themes</h3>
  <p>
    To change the theme for your generated app, access the Theme panel
    in the builder screen and select your preferred theme before generating.
  </p>

  <h3>Theme System</h3>
  <p>
    Each theme defines a set of CSS custom properties that are applied
    to the generated app. The theme system ensures visual consistency
    across all built-in components.
  </p>
</DocsLayout>
